## 11. ğŸ§© Guidance for Future AI Developers

When continuing this project:

1. **Read `docs/react-native-migration.md` first** â€” it defines the architectural strategy.  
2. **Review this guide fully** â€” it sets your constraints and safe operating bounds.  
3. **When proposing code changes**, explain the reasoning and intended effect in a single paragraph before generating the code.  
4. **Never modify Supabase schema** â€” only consume and write via existing functions or hooks.  
5. **Work iteratively** â€” make atomic, reviewable changes per task (UI parity â†’ offline sync â†’ QA).  
6. **Test on device** (Expo Go / EAS preview) before merging any mobile feature.  
7. **Always maintain TypeScript safety** and avoid implicit `any` or untyped Supabase calls.  

When uncertain, query or regenerate this guide for context â€” it is the authoritative project baseline.

